  "prompt": "How did Ocean's Eight (2018 movie) get greenlit? What's the backstory of how the movie got made?",
  "response": "Ocean's Eight was developed as a spin-off/continuation of the Ocean's trilogy starring George Clooney. The idea originated as a female-led heist film in that same universe. Producer Sandra Bullock was instrumental in getting the project moving, and she approached director Gary Ross about making the film. The script was co-written by Ross and Olivia Milch, with Bullock attached to star as Danny Ocean's sister Debbie Ocean.\n\nThe project was pitched as a way to reimagine the Ocean's franchise with a fresh, female-led perspective. Warner Bros. was interested in continuing the franchise after the success of the previous Ocean's films, and saw this as an opportunity to reboot the series with a new ensemble cast.\n\nThe film received support from the original Ocean's trilogy creators, including Steven Soderbergh (who produced this film), and featured a cameo reference to Danny Ocean (George Clooney's character), though Clooney himself did not appear in the movie.\n\nThe star-studded cast, which included Bullock, Cate Blanchett, Anne Hathaway, Mindy Kaling, Sarah Paulson, Awkwafina, Rihanna, and Helena Bonham Carter, was also a key factor in getting the film greenlit and generating excitement around the project.",
